<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="as-pron">as <strong><em>pron</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /əz/    美 /əz/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>(正) 如…一样：</strong></h4>
<ul>
<li>作关系代词，引导限制性定语从句，常与 such和the same连用：</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>He is not such a fool as he looks. 
他并不像看起来那么傻。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The T-shirt I received is not the same as is shown online.
我收到的T恤和网上展示的不一样。</p><footer>2013 江苏</footer></div>

<ul>
<li>作关系代词，引导非限制性定语从句，从句可位于主句前、中、后：</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>As we all know, success comes from hard work. 
众所周知，成功源于勤奋。</p></div>

<h3 id="as-which">辨析 as, which</h3>
<p>二者都可引导非限制性定语从句，指代主句的全部或部分，作从句中的主语或宾语，其用法、意义区别如下：<br />
<strong>1. as</strong> 引导的定语从句可置于主句前，而which引导的不可以。
<strong>2. as</strong> 引导定语从句时，常有“正如”之意，而which没有。</p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The size of the audience, as we had expected, was well over one thousand.
正如我们所料，观众的人数远远超过了1000。</p></div></div>